1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment is the majority report of the committee and replaces the bill with a
55 resolve. The amendment establishes the Commission to Evaluate the Requirements for
66 Licensing of Social Workers and Certification of Behavioral Health Workers. The
77 commission is directed to conduct a holistic evaluation of the process of social work
88 licensure and certification of behavioral health workers, including the development of
99 alternative pathways to licensure and certification. The commission is required to submit
1100 its report to the Joint Standing Committee on Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial
1111 Services no later than December 3, 2025.
12 The amendment also adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause to the bill.
